      "content": "everything feels so permanent. the lawyers, the lawsuits, the look in my wife's eyes when she realizes we're actually losing the house... it's not something you just \"self-compassion\" your way out of. it feels like every direction i move in just makes the mess bigger. sometimes i sit here just thinking about how much simpler it would be if i just didn't have to deal with the fallout anymore. like, if the problem just stopped existing.",
